1619425569.flavorText: "I cast off my carapace to be reborn, just like our glorious Riis."  —Atraks-1, Fallen Exo

2415768376.flavorText: "There is no warrior fiercer than one shielding hatchlings from harm."  —Eliksni proverb

3974038291.flavorText: "The Traveler has shown us that what was broken can be reformed, becoming better than it was before." —Commander Zavala

1467044898.flavorText: Ice can grind mountains to dust. These will get the job done.

2316914168.flavorText: "Go out in a blaze of glory." —Ancient Earth proverb

2780717641.flavorText: "To gain power, you must sacrifice. Exos have known this long before the Guardians' rise."  —Taeko-3

1935198785.flavorText: See the danger, even when it cannot see you.

2321120637.flavorText: The lightning from the farthest cloud strikes the hardest.

3301944824.flavorText: There is no strength in letting go.

1001356380.flavorText: Feast on the sky. Gorge yourself until all starlight has been gnawed to black—then the cosmos will tremble with your roar.

1453120846.flavorText: Those who walk through fire have burned away their fear.

3045642045.flavorText: The manifestation of pseudophotons and impossible math.

1702288800.flavorText: Built for swift movement, they provide unexpected and decisive social benefits.

300502917.flavorText: The equations balance thus: you are diminished, and I am exalted. You are broken, and I am made strong.

1703551922.flavorText: It reflects whatever it sees, no matter how ugly.

1322544481.flavorText: "No great wonder can stand forever if it is constructed on a lie." —Alexei

3316517958.flavorText:
"I don't know what it means
That I am so sad
A legend of bygone days
That I cannot keep out of my mind." —Die Lorelei, Heinrich Heine

3259193988.flavorText: Osmium's existence requires near-divine intervention—a supernova—to forge.

511888814.flavorText: The nature of the secant is to intercept a curve, a role all human relationships likewise fill.

3453042252.flavorText: Always keep one up your sleeve.

461841403.flavorText: The higher your flight, the faster your dive.

1703598057.flavorText: "Trust me, you don't want to be there when he lands."

1849149215.flavorText: Judge us by the enemies we've made.

4284305242.flavorText: Give me your arm, oh bearer mine. Let me help you fill the world with teeth.

4284305243.flavorText: "This won't end well for one of us. And darling, it won't be me." —Self-styled "Lady" Olu Alderdice

419976110.flavorText: Interfaces with synapses (or nearest equivalent) to draw electric power directly from the wearer's body.

419976111.flavorText:
> No one has ever died wearing me.
# It's true. She leaves the unworthy before they fall.

419976108.flavorText: "It is my honor." —Chalco Yong to Ikora Rey

1667080811.flavorText: You can see the point, right? Who wants to team up with one?

1245809814.flavorText: "I call them the Stompies! For when your legs need that extra kick." —Marcus Ren

458095280.flavorText: Whoever survives our passing does so only by our consent.

458095281.flavorText: Conflict Resolution Solution #3479: Leave them to rest wherever they may fall.

458095282.flavorText: "You who seek the Forge: your journey will be long, but your destination is closer than you think." —Ouros

3790373075.flavorText: Designed for the seamless delivery of justice in an unjust world.

1862800746.flavorText: “You are mine, you shall be mine, you and I are one for ever.”
